 “Why will you resolve to die?
Yoruba Lyrics:
Iyemeji ha nse nyin Pe, ife ni Olorun, E ki o ha gb'oro Re? K'e gba ileri Re gbo? W'Oluwa nyin l'odo nyin, Jesu nsun: w'omije Re; Eje Re pelu nke, pe
“Ese ti e o fi ku?”

English Lyrics: Lord Jesus, think on me, And purge away my sin; From earth-born passions set me free. And make me pure within.
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, jo ranti mi, K'o si we 'se mi nu; Gba mi low'ese 'binibi Si we okan mi mo.

English Lyrics: Lord Jesus, think on me, With many a care oppressed; Let me Thy loving servant be, And taste Thy promised rest.
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, jo ranti mi, Em' eni 'nilara: Ki m’ se 'ranse t'o nife Re, Ki m't'o simi Re wo

English Lyrics: Lord Jesus, thing on me, Nor let me go astray; Through darkness and perplexity Point Thou the Heavenly way.
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, jo ranti mi, Ma je ki nsako lo; N'nu 'damu on okun aiye, F'ona orun han mi.

English Lyrics: Lord Jesus, think on me, That when the flood is past, I may the Eternal brightness see, And share Thy joy at last.
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, jo ranti mi, Gba gbogbo re koja Ki nle r'ogo ainipekun, Ki nsi le ba O yo.

English Lyrics: Lord Jesus, think on me, That I may sing above To Father, Holy Ghost, and Thee, The songs of praise and love. Amen
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, jo ranti mi, Ki nle korin loke, Si Baba, Emi at' Iwo, Orin 'yin at'ife. Amin.

English Title: GIVE TO THE WINDS THY FEARS
English Lyrics: Give to the winds thy fears; Hope, and be undismayed; God hears they sighs, and counts thy tears; God shall lift up thy head.
Yoruba Lyrics: F' eru re f' afefe N'ireti ma foya; Olorun gbo 'mikanle re, Yio gb' ori re ga.

English Title: GIVE TO THE WINDS THY FEARS
English Lyrics: Though waves, and clouds and storms He gently clears thy way; Wait thou His time, so shall this night Soon end in joyous day.
Yoruba Lyrics: N' irumi at' iji, Y'o se ona re fefe: Duro de igba Re; oru Y'o pin s'ojo ayo

English Title: GIVE TO THE WINDS THY FEARS
English Lyrics: Thou seest our weakness, Lord; Our hearts are known to Thee; O lifts Thou up the sinking hand, Confirm the feeble kneel.
Yoruba Lyrics: Iwo'r' ailera wa Inu wa n'iwo mo; Gbe owo t'o re si oke M'ekun ailera le

English Title: GIVE TO THE WINDS THY FEARS
English Lyrics: Let us in life, in death, Thy steadfast truth declare, And publish with our latest breath, Thy love and guardian care.
Yoruba Lyrics: K'awa, n'iye n'iku, So oro Re tantan; K'a so tit' opin emi wa, Ife, itoju Re. Amin.

English Title: GOD MOVES IN A MYSTERIOUS WAY
English Lyrics: God moves in a mysterious way. His wonders to perform; He plants His footsteps in the sea. And rides upon the storm.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ona ara l'Olorun wa, Ngba sise Re I'aiye; A nri 'pase Re I'or'okun, O ngun igbi I'esin.

English Title: GOD MOVES IN A MYSTERIOUS WAY
English Lyrics: Deep in unfathomable mines, Of never-failing skill, He treasures up His bright designs, And works His sovereign Will
Yoruba Lyrics: Ona Re enikan ko mo Awamaridi ni; O pa ise ijinle mo, O si nse bi Oba.

English Title: GOD MOVES IN A MYSTERIOUS WAY
English Lyrics: Ye fearful saints fresh courage take; The clouds ye so much dread. Are big with mercy, and shall break In blessings on your head.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ma beru mo, enyin mimo, Orun t'o su be ni, O kun fun anu; y'o r'ojo, Ibukun s'ori nyin.

English Title: GOD MOVES IN A MYSTERIOUS WAY
English Lyrics: Judge not the Lord by feeble sense. But trust Him for His grace; Behind a frowning providence, He hides a smiling face.
Yoruba Lyrics: Mase da Oluwa l'ejo Sugbon gbeke re le; 'Gbati O ro pe O binu Inu Re dun si o.

English Title: GOD MOVES IN A MYSTERIOUS WAY
English Lyrics: His purposes will ripen fast, Unfolding every hour; The bud may have a bitter taste, But sweet will be the flower.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ise Re fere ye wa na, Y'O ma han siwaju; Bi o tile koro l'oni, O mbo wa dun l'ola

English Title: GOD MOVES IN A MYSTERIOUS WAY
English Lyrics: Blind unbelief is sure to err, And scan His work in vain: God is His own interpreter, And He will make it plain. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Afoju ni alaigbagbo, Ko mo 'se Olorun Olorun ni Olutumo. Yo m'ona Re ye ni. Amin.

English Title: OH, FOR A FAITH THAT WILL NOT SHRINK
English Lyrics: Oh, for a faith that will not shrink Though pressed by many a foe; That will not tremble on the brink Of poverty or woe;
Yoruba Lyrics: A ba le n'igbagbo aye, B’o ti wu k'ota po; igbagbo ti ko je mira Fun aini at' osi.

English Title: OH, FOR A FAITH THAT WILL NOT SHRINK
English Lyrics: That will not murmur nor complain Beneath the chastening rod, But, in the hour of grief or pain, Can lean upon its God,
Yoruba Lyrics: Igbagbo ti ko je rahun L'abe ibawi Re; Sugbon ti nsimi l'Olorun, Nigba ibanuje.

English Title: OH, FOR A FAITH THAT WILL NOT SHRINK
English Lyrics: A faith that shines more bright and clear When tempests rage without; That when in danger knows no fear, In darkness feels no doubt.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igbagbo ti ntan siwaju, Gbat' iji 'ponju de Ti ko si je siyemeji, N'nu wahala gbogbo.

English Title: OH, FOR A FAITH THAT WILL NOT SHRINK
English Lyrics: A faith that keeps the narrow way Till life's last spark is fled, And with a pure and heavenly ray Light up a dying bed.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igbagbo ti ngbo'ona toro, Titi emi o pin; Ti y'o si f'imole orun, Tan akete iku.

English Title: OH, FOR A FAITH THAT WILL NOT SHRINK
English Lyrics: Lord, give me such a faith as this, And then, whate'er may come, I taste e'en now the hallowed bliss Of an Eternal Home. Amen
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu f'igbagbo yi fun mi, Nje b;o ti wu k'o ri, Lat' aiye yi lo ngo l'ayo Ilu orun rere. Amin.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics:
My God, my Father, while I stray,
Far from my home, in life's 
rough way,
O teach me from my heart to 
say,
Thy will be done
Yoruba Lyrics: Baba mi, 'gba mba nsako lo, Kuro l'ona Re l'aiye yi; Ko mi ki nle wi bayi pe, Se 'fe Tire.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics: Though dark my path and sad my lot, Let me be still and murmur not; Or breathe the prayer divinely taught, Thy will be done.
Yoruba Lyrics: B'ipin mi l'aiye ba buru, Ko mi ki ngba, ki nmase kun Ki ngbadura t'o ko mi, wipe, Se 'fe Tire.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics: What though in lonely grief I sigh For friends beloved no longer nigh, Submissive still would I reply, “Thy will be done.”
Yoruba Lyrics: B' o ku emi ni kansoso, Ti ara on o re ko si; Ni teriba ngo ma wipe, Se 'fe Tire.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics: If Thou shouldst call me to resign, What most I prize, it ne'er was mine; I only yield Thee what is Thine; “Thy will be done.”
Yoruba Lyrics: B'o fe gba ohun owo mi, Ohun t' o se o won fun mi; Ngo fi fun O, se Tire ni? Se' 'fe Tire.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics: Let but my fainting heart be blest, With Thy sweet Spirit for its guest My God, to Thee I leave the rest. Thy will be done
Yoruba Lyrics: Sa fi Emi Re tu mi n'nu Ki On k' o si ma ba mi gbe; Eyi t'o ku, o d'owo Re, Se 'fe Tire.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics: Renew my will from day to day, Blend it with Thine, and take away, All that now makes it hard to say Thy will be done.
Yoruba Lyrics: Tun 'fe mi se lo jojumo K'O si mu ohun na kuro, Ti ko je k'emi le wipe, Se 'fe Tire.

English Title: MY GOD, MY FATHER, WHILE I STRAY
English Lyrics: Then, when on earth I breathe no more. The prayer, oft mixed with tears before, I'll sing upon a happier shore, Thy will be done. Amen
Yoruba Lyrics: 'Gbat' emi mi ba pin l'aiye, N'ilu t'o dara ju aiye, L'em o ma k'orin na titi, Se 'fe Tire. Amin

English Title: THINE FOR EVER! GOD OF LOVE
English Lyrics: Thine for ever! God of love, Hear us from Thy Throne above; Thine for ever may we be, Here and in eternity.
Yoruba Lyrics: Tire lailai l'awa se Baba, Olorun ife; Je k'a je Tire titi, Laiye yi, ati lailai

English Title: THINE FOR EVER! GOD OF LOVE
English Lyrics: Thine for ever! Lord of life, Shield us through our earthly strife, Thou the Life, the Truth, the Way, Guide us to the realms of day.
Yoruba Lyrics: Tire lailai l'awa se, Ma toju wa l'aiye yi, 'Wo iye, ona oto, To wa si ilu orun

English Title: THINE FOR EVER! GOD OF LOVE
English Lyrics: Thine for ever! Oh, how blest, They who find in Thee their rest! Saviour, Guardian, Heavenly Friend, Oh! defend us to the end!
Yoruba Lyrics: Tire lailai Abukun L'awon t'o se 'simi won! Olugbala, Ore wa, 'Gba 'ja wa ja de opin

English Title: THINE FOR EVER! GOD OF LOVE
English Lyrics: Thine for ever! Shepherd, keep These Thy frail and trembling sheep; Save alone beneath Thy care, Let us all Thy goodness share.
Yoruba Lyrics: Tire lailai- Jesu, pa Awon aguntan Re mo, L'abe iso rere Re Ni k'o pa gbogbo wa mo

English Title: THINE FOR EVER! GOD OF LOVE
English Lyrics: Thine for ever Thou our Guide, All our wants by Thee supplied, All our sins by thee forgiven. Lead us, Lord from earth to Heaven. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Tire lailai Aini wa Ni o je aniyan Re; O ti f'ese wa ji wa, To wa si ibugbe Re. Amin.

English Title: COME; LET US JOIN OUR CHEERFUL SONGS
Yoruba Title: EWA K'A DA ORIN WA PO
English Lyrics: Come, let us join our cheerful songs, With angels round the throne; Ten thousand are their tongues, But all their joys are one.
Yoruba Lyrics: E wa k'a da orin wa po, Mo t'awon Angeli; Egbegberun ni ohun won Okan ni ayo won.

English Title: COME; LET US JOIN OUR CHEERFUL SONGS
Yoruba Title: EWA K'A DA ORIN WA PO
English Lyrics: “Worthy the Lamb that died,” they cry, “To be exalted thus” “Worthy the Lamb,” our lips reply, “For He was slain for us.”
Yoruba Lyrics: Nwon nk'orin pe, “Ola nla ye, Odagutan t'a pa;” K’a gberin pe ola nla ye “Tori o ku fun wa.

English Title: COME; LET US JOIN OUR CHEERFUL SONGS
Yoruba Title: EWA K'A DA ORIN WA PO
English Lyrics: Jesus is worthy to receive, Honor and power divine; And blessings more than we can give, Be, Lord, for ever Thine
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, li o ye lati gba, Ola at'agbara; K'iyin t'enu wa ko le gba, Je Tire, Oluwa.

English Title: COME; LET US JOIN OUR CHEERFUL SONGS
Yoruba Title: EWA K'A DA ORIN WA PO
English Lyrics: Let all that dwell above the sky, And air, and earth, and seas, Conspire to lift Thy glories high, And speak Thine endless praise
Yoruba Lyrics: K'awon t'o wa l'oke orun, At'ile, at' okun; Dapo lati gb' ogo Re ga, Jumo yin ola Re.

English Title: COME; LET US JOIN OUR CHEERFUL SONGS
Yoruba Title: EWA K'A DA ORIN WA PO
English Lyrics: The whole creation join in one, To bless the sacred name, Of Him that sits upon the throne, And to adore the Lamb. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ki gbogbo eda d'ohun po, Lati yin oruko, Enit' o joko l'or'ite, Ki nwon si wole fun. Amin.

Yoruba Title: BUGBE RE TI L'EW A TO
English Lyrics: Pleasant are thy courts above, In the land of light and love; Pleasant are Thy courts below. In this land of sin and woe, Oh my spirit longs and faints For the converse of Thy saints, For the brightness of Thy face, For Thy fullness, God of Grace
Yoruba Lyrics: 'Bugbe Re ti l'ewa to! N'ile 'mole at' ife; Bugbe Re ti l'ewa to! L'aiye ese at' osi; Okan mi nfa nitoto Fun idapo enia Re, Fun imole oju Re, Fun ekun Re, Olorun.

Yoruba Title: BUGBE RE TI L'EW A TO
English Lyrics: Happy birds that sing and fly Round Thy altars, O Most High! Happier souls that find a rest In a Heavenly Father's Breast! Like the wandering dove that found No repose on earth around, They can to their ark repair, And enjoy it ever there.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ayo ba awon eiye, Ti nfo yi pepe Re ka; Ayo okan t'o simi L'aiya Baba l'o poju! Gege b'adaba Noa, Ti ko r' ibi simi le, Nwon pada s'odo Baba, Nwon si nyo titi aiye.

Yoruba Title: BUGBE RE TI L'EW A TO
English Lyrics: Happy souls! Their praises flow Even in this vale of woe; Waters in the desert rise; Manna feeds them from the skies; On they go from strength to strength. Till they reach Thy Throne at length, At Thy feet adoring fall, Who hast led them safe through all.
Yoruba Lyrics: Nwon ko simi iyin won, Ninu aiye osi yi; Omi nsun ni aginju, Manna nt'orun wa fun won; Nwon nlo lat'ipa de 'pa Titi nwon fi yo si o; Nwon si wole l'ese Re, T'o mu won la ewu ja.

Yoruba Title: BUGBE RE TI L'EW A TO
English Lyrics: Lord, be mine this prize to win, Guide me through a world of sin, Keep me by Thy saving grace, Give me at Thy side a place, Sun and shield alike thou art, Guide and guard my erring heart: Grace and glory flow from Thee; Shower, O shower them, Lord, on me! Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Baba, je ki njere be, S'amona mi l'aiye yi; F'ore-ofe pa mi mo, Fun mi l'aye l'odo Re; Iwo l'orun at' Asa, To okan isina mi; Iwo l'Orisun ore, Ro ojo re s'ori mi. Amin.

English Title: LEAD US, HEAVENLY FATHER, LEAD US
English Lyrics: Lead us, heavenly father, lead us O'er the world's tempestuous sea; Guard us, guide us, keep us, feed us, For we have no help but Thee; Yet possessing every blessing, If our God our father be.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ma toju wa baba orun, Larin 'damu aiye yi; Pa wa mo k'o si ma bo wa, A ko n'iranwo miran; Sugbon gbogbo 'bukun l'ani, B'Olorun je baba wa.

English Title: LEAD US, HEAVENLY FATHER, LEAD US
English Lyrics: Saviour, breathe forgiveness o'er us; All our weakness Thou dost know; Thou didst tread this earth before us, Thou didst feel its keenest woe; Lone and dreary, faint and weary, Through the desert thou didst go.
Yoruba Lyrics: Olugbala, dariji wa, Iwo sa m'ailera wa; 'Wo ti rin aiye saju wa, 'Wo ti mo 'se inu re; B'en' ikanu at' alare, L'O ti la 'ginju yi ja

English Title: LEAD US, HEAVENLY FATHER, LEAD US
English Lyrics: Spirit of our God, descending, Fill our hearts with heavenly joy; Love with every passion blending, Pleasure that can never cloy; Thus provided, pardon'd guided Nothing can our peace destroy. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Emi Olorun, sokale, F'ayo orun k'okan wa; K'ife dapo mo iya wa, At' adun ti ki su ni; B' a ba pese fun wa bayi, Ki l'o le mi 'simi wa?

English Lyrics: O Holy Saviour, Friend unseen, The faint, the weak on Thee may lean; Help me, throughout life's varying scene, By faith to cling to Thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu mimo, Ore airi, Oluranlowo alaini, N'nu ayida aiye, ko mi, K'emi le romo O

English Lyrics: Blest with communion so divine, Take what Thou wilt, shall I repine, When, as the branches to the vine, My soul may cling to Thee?
Yoruba Lyrics: Ki nsa n'idapo mimo yi, Gba ohun t'O fe ngo kun bi? B'okan mi, b'eka jara, Ba sa le romo O.

English Lyrics: Far from her home, fatigued, opprest, Here she has found a place of rest; An exile still, yet not unblest, While she can cling to Thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: Are ti m'okan mi pipo, Sugbon O wa r'ibi simi; Ibukun si de s'okan mi, Tori t'o romo O.

English Lyrics: What through the world deceitful prove, And earthly friends and joys remove, With patients uncomplaining love, Still would I cling to Thee
Yoruba Lyrics: B'aiye d'ofo mo mi l'oju B'a gba ore at'ara lo. Ni suru ati l'aibohun L'emi o romo O.

English Lyrics: Often when I seem to tread alone Some barren waste with thorns o'er grown, A voice of love in gentlest tone Whispers, “Still cling to mee,”
Yoruba Lyrics: Gbat' o k' emi nikansos L'arin idamu aiye yi Mo gb' Ohun ifejeje na, Wipe, “Sa romo Mi”.

English Lyrics: Though faith and hope awhile be tried, I ask not, need not aught beside; How safe, how calm, how satisfied, The souls that cling to thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: B'are ba fe mu igbagbo, T'ireti ba si fe saki, Ko si ewu fun okan na, Tori oromo O.

English Lyrics: They fear not life's rough storms to brave, Since Thou art near and strong to save; Nor shudder e'en at death's dark wave, Because they cling to Thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ko beru irumi aiye, Nitori 'Wo wa nitosi, Ki o si gbon b'iku ba de, Tori oromo O

English Lyrics: Blest is my lot, whate'er befall, What can disturb me who appal While as my strength, my rock, my all
Yoruba Lyrics: Ire sa ni l'ohun gbogbo, Wo agbara at'asa mi; Olugbala, ki y'o si nkan, Bi mba ti romo O. Amin

English Lyrics: Ten thousand times ten thousand, In spirkling rainment bright, The armies of the ransomed saints, Throng up the steeps of light, 'Tis finished! all is finished, Their fight with death and sin, Fling open wide the golden gates, And let the victors in.
Yoruba Lyrics: Egbegberun aimoye, Nwon wo aso ala; Ogun awon t'a rapada Nwon kun 'bi 'mole na, Ija won pelu ese, At' iku ti pari, E si 'lekun wura sile, Fun awon asegun.

English Lyrics: What rush of Alleluias, Fills all the earth and sky! What ringing of a thousand harps? Bespeaks the triumph nigh O day, for which creation And all its tribes were made! O joy, for all its former woes, A thousand-fold repaid!
Yoruba Lyrics: Iro Halleluya won, Lo gb'aiye orun kan, Iro Egbegberun Harpu, Ndun pe 'segun de tan; Jo ta s'eda aiye, Ta da orile'de, Ayo nla pa 'banuje re, Ti a fun ni kikun.

English Lyrics: Oh then what raptured greetings, On Canaan's happy shore, What knitting severed friendships up, Where partings are no more! Then eyes with joy shall sparkle That brimmed with tears of late Orphans no longer fatherless, Nor widows desolate.
Yoruba Lyrics: A! ayo t'a ko le so, Leti bebe Kanaan; Idapo nla wo lo to yi, Nibi ta ki pinya, Oju to kun f'ekun ri, Y'o tan 'mole ayo, Ki yio si alaini baba, Opo ki yio si mo

English Lyrics: Bring near Thy great salvation, Thou Lamb for sinners slain, Fill up the roll of thine elect, Then take Thy power and reign, Appear, Desire of Nations, Thine exiles long for home, Show in the heavens Thy promised sign, Thou Prince and Saviour, come. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Mu 'gbala nla Re fun wa Od' aguntan t'a pa, K'oruko awon ayanfe, Mu 'pa re k’o j'oba, Wa, ofe orile ede, Da onde re sile, Wa fi ami 'leri Re han, Wa, Olugbala wa. Amin

English Lyrics: Lord of the worlds above, How pleasant, and how fair, The dwellings of thy love, Thine earthly temples are! To Thine abode My heart aspires, With warm desires, To see my God.
Yoruba Lyrics: Oluwa wa orun! Ago Re l'aiye yi, Ibugbe ife Re, Ewa re ti po to! Okan mi nfa, Lati g'oke S'ibugbe Re, Olorun mi.

English Lyrics: Oh, happy souls that pray, Where God appoints to hear! Oh, happy men that pay Their constant service there! They praise Thee still, And happy they, That love the way, To Zion's hill.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ayo b'awon ti nsin, Nibit' Olorun yan; Ti nwon npara ibe, Lati ma josin won; Nwon nyin O sa Ayo b'awon, T' o fe ona, Oke Sion.

English Lyrics: They go from strength to strength, Through this dark vale of tears, Till each arrives at length! Till each in heaven appears Oh, glorious seat! When God, our King Shall thither bring, Our willing feet!
Yoruba Lyrics: Nwon nlo nipa de 'pa Laiye osi wa yi; Titi nwon fi goke, Ti nwon si yo s'orun, 'Bugbe ogo! Gbat' Olorun Ba m’ese wa, De ibe na

English Lyrics:
God is our Sun and Shield, Our Light and our Defence; With gifts His hand are filled, We draw our blessings thence
Thrice happy he,
O God of Hosts,
Whose spirit trusts, 
Alone in Thee. Amen!
Yoruba Lyrics:
Olorun l'asa wa, Imole at'odi; Owo Re kun f'ebun, A ngba 'bukun nibe, Ayo pupo, Ni fun awon,
To gbekele, Olorun wa. Amin!

English Lyrics: O come, O come, Emmanuel, And ransom captive Israel, That mourns in lonely exile here, Until the Son of God appear. Rejoice! Rejoice! Emmanuel Shall come to thee, O Israel.
Yoruba Lyrics: Sunm' odo wa, Emmanuel, Wa, ra Israeli pada T' o nsofo li oko eru Titi Jesu y'o tun pade, E yo e yo! Emmanuel Yo wa s'odo wa Israel.

English Lyrics: O come, thou Rod of Jesse, free Thine own from satan's tyranny; From depths of hell thy people save And give them victory o'er the grave. Rejoice! Rejoice! Emmanuel Shall come to thee, O Israel.
Yoruba Lyrics: Wa Opa alade Jesse, K' o gba wa l'owo ota wa, Gba wa low' orun apadi Fun wa ni 'segun l'ori 'ku, E yo e yo! Emmanuel Yo wa s'odo wa Israel

English Lyrics: O come, thou Day-spring come and cheer Our spirits by Thine Advent here; Disperse the gloomy clouds of night, And death's dark shadow put to fight, Rejoice! Rejoice! Emmanuel Shall come to thee, O Israel.
Yoruba Lyrics: Sunmo wa Wo ila-orun, Ki bibo Re se tunu wa, Tu gbogbo isudede ka, M'ese ati egbe kuro, E yo e yo! Emmanuel Yo wa s'odo wa Israel

English Lyrics: O come, thou Key of David, come, And open wide our heavenly home, Make safe the way that leads on high, And close the part of misery, Rejoice! Rejoice! Emmanuel Shall come to thee, O Israel
Yoruba Lyrics: Wa Omo lekun Dafidi, Lekun orun y' o si fun O; Tun ona orun se fun wa Jo se ona osi fun wa: E yo e yo! Emmanuel Yo wa s'odo wa Israel

English Lyrics: O come, O come, thou Lord of Might Who to thy tribes, on Sinai's height, In ancient time didst give the law In cloud, and majesty, and awe, Rejoice! Rejoice! Emmanuel Shall come to thee, O Israel
Yoruba Lyrics: Sunmo wa Oluwa ipa, T' o f' ofin fun enia Re Nigbani l’or’ oke Sinai, Nu eru at' agbara nla E yo e yo! Emmanuel Yo wa s'odo wa Israel Amin

English Lyrics: Love divine, all love excelling, Joy of heaven, to earth come down Fix in us thy humble dwelling, All thy faithful mercies crown Jesus, Thou art all compassion Pure unbounded Love Thou art: Visit us with Thy salvation, Enter every trembling heart
Yoruba Lyrics: Ife orun, alailegbe, Ayo orun sokale: Fi okan wa se 'bugbe Re Se asetan anu re; Jesu, iwo ni alanu, Iwo I onibu ife; Fi igbla re be wa wo, M’okan eru wa duro

English Lyrics:
Come, Almighty to deliver, Let us all thy grace receive Suddenly return, and never, Never more thy temples leave. Thee we would be always blessing,
Serve thee as thy Hosts above;
Pray, and praise thee, without 
ceasing
Glory in Thy perfect love.
Yoruba Lyrics:
Wa, Olodumare, gba wa, Fun wa lore-ofe re: Lojiji ni ko pada wa, Ma si fi wa sile mo, Iwo la o ma yin titi, Bi nwon ti nse ni orun:
Iyin wa ki yio lopin,
A o sogo n'nu 'fe Re

English Lyrics: Finish then thy new Creation Pure and spotless let us be: Let us see thy great Salvation, Perfectly restored in Thee. Changed from glory into glory, Till in heaven we take our place: Till we cast our crowns before Thee, Lost in wonder, love, and praise. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Sasepe awa eda Re, Je ka wa lailaibawon: Ka ri titobi gbala Re, Li aritan ninu Re, Mu wa l'at' Ogo de Ogo Titi de ibugbe wa: Titi awa o fi wole, N'iyanu ife, iyin. Amin.

English Title: ON JORDAN'S BANK, THE BAPTISTS CRY
English Lyrics: On Jordan's bank, the Baptist's cry, Announces that the Lord is nigh Awake, and hearkens, for He brings Glad tidings of the King of kings.
Yoruba Lyrics: L'eba odo Jordani ni, Onibaptisi nke wipe; Oluwa mbo Oluwa mbo E gbo 'hin ayo; Oba mbo.

English Title: ON JORDAN'S BANK, THE BAPTISTS CRY
English Lyrics: Then cleansed be every breast from sin: Make straight the way for God within; Prepare we in our hearts a home Where such a mighty Guest may come.
Yoruba Lyrics: K'ese tan ni gbogbo okan, K'Olorun ba le ba wa gbe K'a pa ile okan wa mo Ki Alejo nla yi to de.

English Title: ON JORDAN'S BANK, THE BAPTISTS CRY
English Lyrics: For thou art our Salvation, Lord Our Refuge and our great Reward: Without Thy grace we waste away, Like flowers that wither and decay
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu, iwo n' igbala wa, Esan ati alabo wa; B'itanna l’awa ba segbe Bikose t'ore-ofe Re.

English Title: ON JORDAN'S BANK, THE BAPTISTS CRY
English Lyrics: To heal the sick, stretch out Thine hand And bid the fallen sinner stand: Shine forth, and let Thy Light restore, Earth's own true loveliness once more.
Yoruba Lyrics: S'awotan awon alaisan, Gb' elese t'o subu dide; Tan mole Re ka bi gbogbo, Mu ewa aiye bo s'ipo

English Title: ON JORDAN'S BANK, THE BAPTISTS CRY
English Lyrics: All praise, Eternal Son, to Thee, Whose Advent doth Thy people free; Whom with the Father we adore, And Holy Ghost for evermore. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: K'a f'iyin f'omo Olorun, Bibo eni mu dande wa; Eni t'a nsin pelu Baba, At’ Olorun Emi Mimo. Amin

English Title: AS WITH GLADNES MEN OF OLD
English Lyrics: As with gladness men of old Did the guiding star behold? As with joy they hailed its light, Leading onward, beaming bright; So, most gracious Lord, may we Evermore be led to Thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: B' awon ara igbani Ti f'ayo ri 'rawo na; Bi nwon ti f'inu didun Tele 'mole didan re; Be Oluwa Olore Ni k'a mu wa d'odo Re.

English Title: AS WITH GLADNES MEN OF OLD
English Lyrics: As with joyful steps they sped, Saviour, to Thy lowly bed, There to bend the knee before Thee Whom Heaven and earth adore; So may we with willing feet Ever seek Thy mercy-seat.
Yoruba Lyrics: Bi nwon ti fi ayo lo Si ibuje eran na; Ti nwon si wole nibe F'Eni t'orun t'aiye mbo; Gege be ni k'a ma yo Lati wa s'ite anu

English Title: AS WITH GLADNES MEN OF OLD
English Lyrics: As they offered gifts most rare, At that manger rude and bare; So may we with holy joy Pure and free from sin's alloy, All our costly treasures bring Christ! to Thee our heavenly King.
Yoruba Lyrics: Bi nwon ti mu ore wa Si ibuje eran na; Be ni k'awa ma f'ayo Mimo t'ese ko baje Mu 'sura wa gbogbo, wa Sodo Re, Jesu Oba.

English Title: AS WITH GLADNES MEN OF OLD
English Lyrics: Holy Jesus, every day Keep us in the narrow way; And, when earthly things are past, Bring our ransomed souls at last Where they need no star to guide Where no clouds Thy glory hide
Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu mimo, pa wa mo, L'ona toro l'ojojo; 'Gbat' ohun aiye ba pin, M'okan wa de ilu, ti 'Rawo ko nsamona mo; Biti nwon nwo ogo Re

English Title: AS WITH GLADNES MEN OF OLD
English Lyrics: In the heavenly country bright Need they no created light; Thou its Light, its Joy, its Crown, Thou its Sun which goes not down; There for ever may we sing Alleluias to our King. Amen
Yoruba Lyrics: Ni 'lu orun Mimo na, Nwon ko wa imole mo; 'Wo l'Orun re ti ki wo; 'Wo l'ayo at' ade re; Nibe titi l'ao ma ko Halleluya s'Oba wa. Amen.

English Title: O GOD, OUR HELP IN AGES PAST.
English Lyrics: O God, our Help in ages past Our hope for years to come, Our Shelter from the stormy blast, And our Eternal Home.
Yoruba Lyrics: Olorun, t'odun t'o koja Iret' eyi ti mbo; Ib' isadi wa ni iji, At' ile wa lailai.

English Title: O GOD, OUR HELP IN AGES PAST.
English Lyrics: Beneath the shadow of thy Throne Thy Saints have dwelt secure; Sufficient is Thine Arm alone, And our defence is sure.
Yoruba Lyrics: Labe ojiji ite Re L'awon enia Re ngbe! Tito l'apa Re nikanso, Abo wa si daju.

English Title: O GOD, OUR HELP IN AGES PAST.
English Lyrics: Before the hills in order stood, Or earth received her frame, From everlasting Thou art God, To endless years the Same.
Yoruba Lyrics: K'awon oke k'o to duro, Tabi k'a to d'aiye Lailai iwo ni Olorun Bakanna, lailopin!

English Title: O GOD, OUR HELP IN AGES PAST.
English Lyrics: A thousand ages in Thy sight Are like an evening gone; Short as the watch that ends the night Before the rising sun
Yoruba Lyrics: Egberun odun loju Re, Bi ale kan l'o ri; B' iso kan l'afemojumo, Ki orun k'o to la.

English Title: O GOD, OUR HELP IN AGES PAST.
English Lyrics: Time, like an ever-rolling stream, Bears all its sons away They fly forgotten, as a dream Dies at the opening day.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ojo wa, bi odo sisan, Opo l'o si ngbe lo; Nwon nlo, nwon di eni 'gbagbe Bi ala ti a nro

English Title: O GOD, OUR HELP IN AGES PAST.
English Lyrics: O God, our help in ages past, Our Hope for years to come; Be Thou our Guard while life shall last, And our Eternal home. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Olorun t' odun t'o koja Iret' eyi ti mbo, Ma s'abo wa 'gba 'yonu de At' ile wa lailai. Amin.

English Title: CHRIST, WHOSE GLORY FILLS THE SKIES
English Lyrics: Christ, Whose glory fills the skies, Christ, the true, the only Light, Sun of Righteousness, arise, Triumph o'er the shades of night; Dayspring from on high, be near, Daystar, in my heart appear.
Yoruba Lyrics: Krist,Ologo, Olola, Iwo imole aiye Orun ododo, dide K' o si bori Okunkun; 'Mole oro sunmo mi; 'Rawo oro w'aiya mi.

English Title: CHRIST, WHOSE GLORY FILLS THE SKIES
English Lyrics: Dark and cheerless is the morn Unaccompanied by Thee: Joyless is the day's return, Till Thy mercy's beams I see; Till they inward light impart, Glad my eyes, and warm my heart.
Yoruba Lyrics: Okunkun l'owuro je B'Iwo ko pelu re wa; Ailayo l'ojo yi je, B'anu ko tan mole mi, Fun mi n' imole, Jesu M' okan mi gbogbo gbona.

English Title: CHRIST, WHOSE GLORY FILLS THE SKIES
English Lyrics: Visit then this soul of mine, Pierce the gloom of sin and grief; Fill me, Radiancy Divine, Scatter all my unbelief; More and more Thyself display, Shining to the perfect day
Yoruba Lyrics: Wa be okan mi yi wo, Le okunkun ese lo: F'imole orun kun mi, Si tu aigbagbo mi ka, Ma f'ara Re han mi si, Si ma ran b' osangangan

English Title: MY TIME ARE IN THY HAND
Yoruba Title: IGBA MI NBE NI OWO RE
English Lyrics: My times are in Thy hand, My God, I wish them there; My life, my friends, my soul I leave Entirely to Thy care.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igba mi mbe li owo Re, A fe k'o wa nibe; A f'ara wa at'ore wa Si abe iso Re.

English Title: MY TIME ARE IN THY HAND
Yoruba Title: IGBA MI NBE NI OWO RE
English Lyrics: My times are in Thy hand, Why should I doubt or fear? A Father's Hand will never cause His child a needless tear.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igba mi mbe li owo Re, Awa o se beru? Baba ki y'o je k'omo Re, Sokun li ainidi.

English Title: MY TIME ARE IN THY HAND
Yoruba Title: IGBA MI NBE NI OWO RE
English Lyrics: My times are in Thy Hand, Whatever they may be, Pleasing or painful, dark or bright, As best may seem to thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igba mi mbe li owo Re, 'Wo l'a o gbekele; Tit' a o f'aiye osi 'le T' a o si r'ogo Re.

English Title: MY TIME ARE IN THY HAND
Yoruba Title: IGBA MI NBE NI OWO RE
English Lyrics: My times are in Thy hand, Jesus the crucified; The Hand my cruel sins, had pierced Is now my guard and guide,
Yoruba Lyrics: Igba mi mbe li owo Re, Jesu t'agbelebu; Owo na t'ese mi dalu, Wa di alabo mi.

English Title: MY TIME ARE IN THY HAND
Yoruba Title: IGBA MI NBE NI OWO RE
English Lyrics: My times are in Thy hand, I'll always trust in Thee, And after death at Thy right Hand I shall for ever be. Amen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igba mi mbe li owo Re: Ngo ma simi le O, Lehin iku, l'ow' otun Re, L'em' o wa titi lai. Amin.

English Lyrics: Come ye thankful people, come, Raise the song of harvest home! All is safely gathered in, Ere the winter storms begin: God our maker, doth provide For our wants to be supplied Come to God's own Temple, come, Raise the song of Harvest home!
Yoruba Lyrics: Wa, eyin olope, wa, Gbe orin ikore ga: Ire gbogbo ti wole K' otutu oye to de: Olorun Eleda wa L'o ti pese f'aini wa; Wa k' a re 'le Olorun Gbe orin ikore ga.

English Lyrics: All the world is God's own field, Fruit unto His praise to yield: Wheat and tares together sown, Unto joy or sorrow grown: First the blade, and then the ear, Then the full corn shall appear: Lord of Harvest, grant that we Wholesome grain and pure may be.
Yoruba Lyrics: Oko Olorun l'aiye, Lati s'eso iyin Re; Alikama at'epo Ndagba f' aro tab' ayo: Ehu na, ipe tele, Siri oka nikehin; Oluwa kore, mu wa Je eso rere fun O

English Lyrics: For the Lord our God shall come, And shall take His harvest Home: From His field shall in that day All offences purge away: Give his Angels charge at last In the fire the tears to cast: But the fruitful ears to store In His garner evermore.
Yoruba Lyrics: N'tori Olorun wa mbo Y' o si kore Re sile; On o gbon gbogbo panti Kuro l'oko Re n'jo na: Y'o f'ase, f'awon Angel' Lati gba epo s'ina, Lati ko alikama Si aba Re titi lai.

English Lyrics: Even so, Lord, quickly come To Thy final Harvest-home; Gather Thou Thy people in, Free from sorrow, free from sin; There, for ever purified, In Thy presence to abide: Come, with all Thine Angels, come; Raise the glorious Harvesthome! Amen
Yoruba Lyrics: Beni ma wa Oluwa Si ikore ikehin; Ko awon enia Re jo Kuru l'ese at aro: So won di mimo lailai Ki nwon le ma ba O gbe: Wa t'Iwo t' Angeli Re Gbe orin ikore ga. Amin.

English Lyrics: Come, women, wide proclaim Life through your savior slain Sing evermore, Christ, God's effulgence bright Christ, who arose in might Christ, who crowns you with light, praise and adore
Yoruba Lyrics: Wa, obinrirn, eko Orin iye nipa Olugbala Kristi, mole Olorun, Kristi, t'ojinde nipa Krist' to' de nyin lade On ni k'e yin

Yoruba Lyrics: Eko awon omode Ati arabirin, n'ile gbogbo Fun awon elese, F'awon alailera At'eni okunkun, Ma gbadur

Yoruba Lyrics: 'Gbati 'kore ba de Aka Oluwa wa Yo kun pupo 'Reti onirele Krist, ti gbogbo wa nwa Krist, y'o fun nyin l'ere Pelu Ayo.

English Lyrics: Sing them over again to me Wonderful words of life Let me more of their beauty see Wonderful words of life Words of life and beauty, Teach me faith and duty

Yoruba Lyrics: Oro didun! Oro 'yanu Oro 'yanu t'iye 2/ce

Yoruba Lyrics: Kristi nikan lo nfi fun ni Oro 'yanu t'iye Elese gbo 'pe ife na Oro 'yanu t'iye L'ofe la fifun wa, ko le to wa s'orun

Yoruba Lyrics: Gbo ohun ihinrere na Oro 'yanu t'iye F'igbala lo gbogbo eniyan Oro 'yanu t'iye Jesu Olugbala, we wa mo titi lai

English Lyrics:
Saviour, a-gain to Thy dear name we raise With one accord our part-ing hymn of praise Once more we bless Thee ere our wor-ship cease 
Then, low-ly kneel-ing, wait 
Thy word of peace

Yoruba Lyrics: F'alafia fun wa ni aye wa Re wa lekun, k'o si gbe wa n'ija 'Gbat' oba si f'opin s'idamu wa Pe wa, Baba, s'orun alafia

English Lyrics: Stand up, and bless the Lord Ye peo-ple of His choice Stand up, and bless the Lord your God With heart and soul and voice.

English Lyrics: Though high a-bove all praise A-bove all bless-ing high Who would not fear His ho-ly Name And laud and mag-ni-fy?

English Lyrics: Oh, for the liv-ing flame From His own altar brought To touch our lips, our minds in-spire And wing to heav'n our thought!

Let us each, Thy love pos sessing

Yoruba Title: FI IBUKUN RE TU WA KA

Yoruba Title: FI IBUKUN RE TU WA KA

Yoruba Lyrics: Af'ope f'olorun L'okan ati ohun wa Eni s'ohun 'yanu N'nu Enit' araiye nyo Gbat' a wa l'a mowo On na l'o nto ju wa O si nf'ebun ife Se to ju wa sibe

English Lyrics: O may this bounteous God Through all our life be near us With ever joyful hearts And bless-ed peace to cheer us And keep us in His grace And guide us when perplexed And free us from all ills In this world and the next
Yoruba Lyrics: Oba onibuore Ma fi wa sile lailai Ayo ti ko lopin On bukun yio je ti wa Pa wa mo n;nu ore To wa gba ba damu Yo wa ninu ibi L'aiye ati l'orun

Yoruba Lyrics: K'a fiyin on ope F'Olorun Baba Omo Ati Emi mimo Ti o ga julo l'orun Olorun kan lailai T'aiye at'orun mbo Be l'o wa d'isiyi Beni yo wa lailai

Yoruba Lyrics: Gbat' ile ba simo je k'emi dide b'omo ti ko l'ese Ni iwaju Re. Amen.

English Lyrics: There's not a friend like the lowly Jesus No, not one! No, not one! None else could heal all our soul's dis-eas-es No, not one! No, not one!
Yoruba Lyrics: Ko s'ore bi Jesu onirele Ko s'okan! Ko s'okan! Ko selomi to le w'okan wa san Ko s'okan! Ko s'okan!

Yoruba Lyrics: Jesu mo gbogbo idamu wa Y'o toju wa dopin ojo Ko s'ore bi Jesu onirele Ko s'okan! Ko s'okan!

Yoruba Lyrics: Enikan ha ti r'ore yi nko ni? Ko s'okan! Ko s'okan! Ta b'elese ri ko ni gba on la? Ko s'okan! Ko s'okan!

Wonderful story of love; Jesus provides a rest, Wonderful story of love; For all the pure and blest, Rest in those mansions above us, With those who've gone on before us,
Singing the rapturous chorus,
Wonderful story of love.

English Lyrics: Faith of our fathers! we will strive To win all nations unto thee, And through the truth that comes from God Mankind shall then be truly free: Faith of our fathers! Holy faith! We will be true to Thee till death.
Yoruba Lyrics: Igbagbo awon baba wa, A o feran ore at'ota, A o si f'ife nla rohin re Ninu oro at' ise wa; Igbagbo mimo ti baba! A o j' olooto si O do'pin.

English Title: DEEPER, DEEPER IN THE LOVE OF JESUS
Yoruba Title: MO FE JINLE SII NINU IFE JESU
English Lyrics: Deeper, deeper, in the love of Jesus Daily let me go; Higher, higher in school of wisdom More of grace to kno

English Title: DEEPER, DEEPER IN THE LOVE OF JESUS
Yoruba Title: MO FE JINLE SII NINU IFE JESU
English Lyrics: O deep … er yet I pray … And high … er every day … And wis … er, blessed Lord, In Thy precious holy word…
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe … maa jinle sii… Ki n ga… sii n joojumo, Ki nsi…ni ogbon sii… N'nu oro yebiye Re.

English Title: DEEPER, DEEPER IN THE LOVE OF JESUS
Yoruba Title: MO FE JINLE SII NINU IFE JESU
English Lyrics: Deeper, deeper! blessed Holy Spirit, Take me deeper still, Till my life is wholly lost in Jesus And His perfect wil
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe jinle. Iwo Emi Mimo, Mu mi jinle si i, Ti gbogb'aye mi yoo je ti Jesu Ati ife Re.

English Title: DEEPER, DEEPER IN THE LOVE OF JESUS
Yoruba Title: MO FE JINLE SII NINU IFE JESU
English Lyrics: Deeper, deeper! though it cost hard trials, Deeper let me go! Rooted in the holy love of Jesus, Let me fruitful grow.
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe jinle, b'idanwo tile de, Mu mijinle si i, Ki n fi gbongbo mule n'nu fe Jesu, Je ki n s'eso si i.

English Title: DEEPER, DEEPER IN THE LOVE OF JESUS
Yoruba Title: MO FE JINLE SII NINU IFE JESU
English Lyrics: Deeper, higher every day in Jesus, till all conflict past, Finds me conqu'ror, and in His own image Perfected at last.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ki n jinle, ki n dagba ninu Jesu, Tit'ija yoo tan, Si se mi ni asegun bi i ti Re Titi de opin.

English Title: GIVE OF YOUR BEST TO THE MASTER
English Lyrics: Give of your best to the master; Give of the strength of your youth; Throw your soul's fresh, glowing ardor Into the battle for truth. Jesus has set the example; Dauntless was He, young and brave; Give Him your loyal devotion, Give Him the best that you have
Yoruba Lyrics: F' eyi t'o s owon f'Oluwa' F'okun gba ewe re fun un; F'ina itara okan re Sinu ija f'otito, Jesu ti fun wa l'apere, O j'akinkanju l'ewe F'otito okan re fun un, F'eyi t'o s'owon re fun un

English Title: GIVE OF YOUR BEST TO THE MASTER
English Lyrics: Give of your best to the master: Give of the strength of your youth Clad in salvation's full armor, Join in the battle for truth.
Yoruba Lyrics: F'eyi t'o s'owon f'Oluwa F'okun gba ewe re fun un Gbe 'hamora igbala wo, Darapo, ja f'otito.

English Title: GIVE OF YOUR BEST TO THE MASTER
English Lyrics: Give of your best to the master; Give Him first place in your heart; Give first place in your service, Conecrate ev'ry part. Give, and to you shall be given; God His beloved Son gave; Gratefully seeking to serve Him Give Him the best that you have
Yoruba Lyrics: F'eyi t'o s'owon f'oluwa, Fi s'akoko l'okan re, Fi s'akoko n'u isin re, Fi gbogbo ipa ji fun un, Fi fun-ni, a o si fi fun o, Baba f'Omo Re fun wa, F'ayo s'aferi lati sin in, F'eyi t'o s'owon re fun un.

English Title: GIVE OF YOUR BEST TO THE MASTER
English Lyrics:
Give of the best to your master; Naught else is worthy His love; He gave Himself for your ransom, Gave up His glory above: Laid down His life without 
Murmur,
You from sin's ruin to save;
Give Him your heart's
Yoruba Lyrics:
F'eyi t'o s'owon f'Oluwa, Ko s'oun miiran t'o ye fun un, O f' ara Re rubo fun o O f' ogo Re orun le, O f'emi Re le le laikun, Lati gba o low' ese
Fi iyin okan re fun un,
F'eyi t'o s'owon re fun un.

English Title: O LOVE THAT WILL NOT LET ME GO
Yoruba Title: IFE TI KO JE KI N SAKO
English Lyrics: O love that will not let me go I rest my weary soul in Thee: I give Thee back the life I owe, That in Thine ocean depths its flow May richer, fuller be.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ife ti ko je ki n salo, Mo wa sinmi le aya Re; Mo f'aye mi fun o pada, K'o le wo 'nu ife Re lo, Ki n le tubo fe O.

English Title: O LOVE THAT WILL NOT LET ME GO
Yoruba Title: IFE TI KO JE KI N SAKO
English Lyrics: O light that follow'st all my way, I yield my flick' ring torch to Thee: My heart restores its borrow'd Ray That in Thy sunshine's blaze its day. May brighter, fairer be
Yoruba Lyrics: Imole ti ntan l'ona mi, Ngo maa tele ipase Re Da tansan okan mi pada, Ki ojo re le mole si i, N'nu oorun Re ti n ran.

English Title: O LOVE THAT WILL NOT LET ME GO
Yoruba Title: IFE TI KO JE KI N SAKO
English Lyrics: O Joy that seekest me through pain, I cannot close my heart to Thee; I trace the rainbow through the rain, And feel the promise is not vain, That morn shall tearless be
Yoruba Lyrics: Iwo l'ayo mi n'nu ponju, N ko le se okan mi fun O Mo r' osumare n'nu ojo Ileri naa da mi loju Ooro ayo de tan.

English Title: O LOVE THAT WILL NOT LET ME GO
Yoruba Title: IFE TI KO JE KI N SAKO
English Lyrics:
O Cross that liftest up my head, I dare not ask to hide from Thee: I lay in dust life's glory dead, And from the ground there blossoms red
Life that shall endless be.
Yoruba Lyrics: Iwo l'o n gb' ori mi soke, N ko jelo kuro lodo Re; Gba t'aye doju mi bole, Wo gbe mi dide n'ireti S'iye ainipekun

English Lyrics: Master the tempest is raging! The billows are tossing high! The sky is o'er-shadowed with blackness, No shelter or help is nigh: “Carest Thou not that we perish?” How canst Thou lie asleep, When each moment so madly is threatening A grave in the angry deep?
Yoruba Lyrics: Oluwa iji n fe soke! Igbi omi n ru soke! Wo o b' oju orun ti su dede, Ranlowo ko si n' tosi? Eese t'Iwo fi n sun, N' igba t'igbi n deruba wa wi pe Omi ni iboju wa?

English Lyrics: “The winds and the waves shall obey My will, Peace, be still” Whether the wrath of the storm-tossed sea, Or demons, or men, or whatever it be, No water can swallow the ship where it lies The master of ocean and earth and skies; They all shall sweetly obey My will Peace be still! Peace, be still
Yoruba Lyrics: “Afefe at'igbi yoo se 'fe mi, Dake jee!” Ibaa se 'binu riru okun, Ibaa s'emi esu, tab'ohunkohun, Ko si omi ti o le ri oko Ti Oluwa orun at'aye wa, Won yoo f'inu didun se 'fe mi Dake, jeje!

English Lyrics:
Master, with anguish of spirit I bow in my grief today; The depths of my sad heart are troubled;
O waken and save, I pray!
Torrents of sin and of anguish
Sweep o'er my sinking soul!
And I perish! I perish, dear 
Master;
O hasten, and take control!
Yoruba Lyrics:
Jesu, iwo ri edun mi, Mo wole n'ibinuje, Ibanuje ti bo okan mi, Dide k' O ran mi lowo1
Ese ti mu 're wesi wa
Okan mi n fa sehin!
Aa! Oluwa, Okan mi n segbe 
lo,
Yara, gb'ori mi soke,

English Lyrics: Master, the terror is over, The elements sweetly rest; Earth's sun in the calm lake is mirrored, And heaven's within my breast Linger O blessed Redeemer, Leave me alone no more; And with joy I shall make the blest harbor, And rest of the blissful shore.
Yoruba Lyrics: Oluwa, eru ti koja, Iparoro nla si de Oorun f'oju han lor' agbami, Orun si wa l'aya mi, Duro, Olurapada mi, Ma fi mi sile mo, Pel' ayo n o d'ebute ibukun N' o sinmi titi aye.

English Lyrics: I'll tell to all that God is love; For the world has never known The great compassion of His Heart For the wayward and the lone.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ngo so 'fe Olorun f'aye, Tori aye ko ti i mo; Ti aanu t'o wa l'okan Re Fun awon t'o ti sako

English Lyrics: Till the whole world knows, Till the whole world knows, I will shout and sing of Christ my King Till the whole world knows.
Yoruba Lyrics: Tit'aye yoo gbo, Tit'aye yoo gbo, Emi yoo rohin Krist' Oba mi, Tit'aye yoo gbo.

English Lyrics:
I'll tell of mercy's boundless tide, Like the water of the sea That covers ev'ry sin of man;
'Tis salvation full and free
Yoruba Lyrics: N o rohin t'aanu ailopin Gege bi omi Okun, T'o bo gbogb'ese eniyan, Igbala ofe l'eyi.

English Lyrics: I'll tell of grace that keep the Soul, Of abiding peace within, Of faith that overcomes the world, With its tumult and sin.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ti oor'ofe t'o n p'okan mo, T'alaafia t'o wa ninu, T'igbagbo t'o bori aye Pelu wa'ala inu re

English Lyrics: Eternal is the goal That awaits the son of light; Eternal darkness, black as death, For the children of the night.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ile-ogo n'ilepa naa T'o n duro d'omo 'mole; Ookun ayeraye bi iku, F'awon omo okunkun.

English Lyrics: How to reach the masses, men of every birth, For an answer Jesus gave the key; “And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, I'll draw all men unto Me
Yoruba Lyrics: A o ti se wasu fun gbogbo aye? Fun idahun re, Jesu wi pe; “Bi a ba le gbe mi soke n'nu aye, Ngo f'awon si odo mi”

English Lyrics: Lift Him up…Lift Him up… Still He speaks from eternity: “And I, if I be lifted up from the earth, I'll draw all men unto Me.”
Yoruba Lyrics: Gbe E soke, Gbe E soke? B'Oun ti wi l'at'ayeraye: Bi a ba le gbe mi soke n'nu aye, “Ngo f'awon si odo mi”.

English Lyrics:
Oh! The world is hungry for the living bread, Lift the Saviour up for them to see; Trust Him, and do not doubt the words that He said,
“I'll draw all men unto Me.”
Yoruba Lyrics: Aah! Oungbe n gbe aye f'ounje iye wa, Gbe Jesu s'oke ki won le ri; Gbagbo ma siyemeji si oro naa, “N o f'awon si odo mi.”

English Lyrics: Don't exalt the preacher, don't exalt the pew, Preach the gospel simple, full and free; Prove Him and you will find that Promise is true, “I'll draw all men unto me.”
Yoruba Lyrics: Ma se gb'alore ga ati pepe Re, Waasu 'hin-rere pipe l'ofee; To O wo, wo yoo mo p'ooto n'ileri naa: “Ngo f'awon si odo mi.”

English Lyrics: Lift Him up by living as a Christian ought, Let the world in you the Saviour see; Then men will gladly follow Him who once taught “I'll draw all men unto me.”
Yoruba Lyrics: Fi Jesu han nipa igbe aye Re. Je ki aye ri n'nu re; Gbogb' eeyan yoo si tel'Emi t'O wi pe: “Ngo f'awon si odo mi.”

English Title: I LOVE TO TELL THE STORY
Yoruba Title: MO FE MAA SO ITAN NAA.
English Lyrics: I love to tell the story of unseen things above, Of Jesus and His glory, of Jesus and His love; I love to tell the story because I know 'tis true, It satisfies my longings as nothing else can do.
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe maa so itan ohun t'orun t'a ko ri Nipa Jesu at'ogo Re, at'ife nla Re: Mo fe maa so itan naa, mo mo pe ooto ni, Itan naa n fun mi layo ju ohun gbogbo lo.

English Title: I LOVE TO TELL THE STORY
Yoruba Title: MO FE MAA SO ITAN NAA.
English Lyrics: I love to tell the story! 'T'will be my theme in gloryTo tell the old, old story Of Jesus and His love
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe maa so itan naa! Yoo j'orin mi nin'ogo Lati so 'tan igbaani, Ti Jesu oun 'fe Re

English Title: I LOVE TO TELL THE STORY
Yoruba Title: MO FE MAA SO ITAN NAA.
English Lyrics: I love to tell the story 'tis pleasant to repeat What seems, each time I tell it, more wonderfully sweet; I love to tell the story, for some have never heard The message of Salvation from God's own holy Word.
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe maa so itan naa- o dun lati fun un so. Didun ni l'ojojumo, o n ya mi lenu sii: Mo fe maa so itan naa, pupo ni ko ti i gbo, Itan igbala kikun lat'inu Oro Re

English Title: I LOVE TO TELL THE STORY
Yoruba Title: MO FE MAA SO ITAN NAA.
English Lyrics: I love to tell the story, for those who knows it best Seem hungering and thirsting to hear it like the rest; And when in scenes of glory I sing the new, new song, 'Twill be the old, old story That I have loved so long
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo fe maa so itan naa, opo ni oungbe n gbe, Won n s'aferi lati gbo itan iyanu yii; Gba mo ba de 'nu ogo, n o ko orin titun, Orin itan 'yanu yii ni n o maa ko titi.

English Title: AND CAN IT BE THAT I SHOULD GAIN
Yoruba Title: O HA LE JE PE MO NI IPIN
English Lyrics: And can it be, that I should gain An interest in the Saviour's blood? Died He for me, who caused His pains? For me, who Him to death pursued? Amazing love! how can it be That Thou, my God, shouldst die for me?
Yoruba Lyrics: O ha le je pe mo n'ipin Ninu eje Olugbala; P'O ku f'emi t'o da A l'oro, T'o pon On loju titi de ku; Ife yanu, ee ha ti se, T'Iwo Oluwa ku fun mi?

English Title: AND CAN IT BE THAT I SHOULD GAIN
Yoruba Title: O HA LE JE PE MO NI IPIN
English Lyrics:
Tis mystery all! The immortal dies! Who can explore His strange design? In vain the first-born seraph 
tries
To sound the depth of love 
divine!
'Tis mercy all! let earth adore,
Let angel-minds inquire no 
more.
Yoruba Lyrics:
Ohun jinle pe Jesu ku, Taa ni mo idi ete Re? Lasan ni angeli wadi Lati mo jinle ife naa! Aanu nikan lo mu k'O ku,
Ki angeli ma wadi mo.

English Title: AND CAN IT BE THAT I SHOULD GAIN
Yoruba Title: O HA LE JE PE MO NI IPIN
English Lyrics: He left His Father's throne above So free, so infinite His grace Emptied Himself of all but love And bled for Adam's helpless race: 'Tis mercy all, immense and free, For, O my God, it found out me!
Yoruba Lyrics: O f'ite Baba Re sile, Oore-ofe Re ko l'opin, O bo gbogbo'ogo Re sile, O ku fun iran Adamu Aanu nikan, aanu ofe, L'o wa mi ri, Olorun mi.

English Title: AND CAN IT BE THAT I SHOULD GAIN
Yoruba Title: O HA LE JE PE MO NI IPIN
English Lyrics: Long my imprisoned spirit lay Fast bound in sin and nature's night; Thine eye diffused a quickening ray, I woke, the dungeon flamed with light; My chains fell off, my heart was free, I rose, went forth, and followed Thee.
Yoruba Lyrics: O pe t'a ti de okan mi Sinsin pelu ewon ese, Oju Re tan 'mole iye, Mo taji imole wole, Ewon mi bo, mo d'om nira, Mo dide mo si n to O lehin.

English Title: AND CAN IT BE THAT I SHOULD GAIN
Yoruba Title: O HA LE JE PE MO NI IPIN
English Lyrics:
No condemnation now I dread, Jesus, and all in Him, is mine; Alive in Him my living Head, And clothed in Righteousness Divine Bold I approach the eternal throne, And claim the crown, through
Christ my own.
Yoruba Lyrics: Emi ko jaya ebi mo, T'emi n’Kristi patapata, Emi wa laaye ninu Re, O gbe ododo Re wo mi, Nigboya , mo sunmo ite, Mo gb'ade l'agbara Kristi.

English Title: TELL ME THE OLD, OLD STORY
English Lyrics: Tell me the old, old story, Of unseen things above Of Jesus and His glory, Of Jesus and His love; Tell me the story simple, As to a little child, For I am weak and weary, And helpless and defiles
Yoruba Lyrics: So 'tan igbaani fun mi, T'ohun ti n be l'orun, Ti Jesu ati ogo Re, Ati ti ife Re, So itan kan naa fun mi, B'a tin so f'omode, Tor'alailera l'emi, Emi ko si l'okun.

English Title: TELL ME THE OLD, OLD STORY
English Lyrics: Tell me the old, old story, Tell me the old, old story, Tell me the old, old story, Of Jesus and His love.
Yoruba Lyrics: So itan kan naa fun mi (3ce) Ti Jesu oun 'fe Re.

English Title: TELL ME THE OLD, OLD STORY
English Lyrics: Tell me the story slowly, That I may take it in That wonderful redemption, God's remedy for sin; Tell me the story often, For I forget so soon, The “early dew” of morning Has passed away at noon.
Yoruba Lyrics: So 'tan naa fun mi pele, Ki o ba le ye mi, T'irapada iyanu, T'etutu fun ese, So fun mi nigba gbogbo, Tori n ki pe gbagbe! Oye ori mi to lo, Bi iri owuro.

English Title: TELL ME THE OLD, OLD STORY
English Lyrics: Tell me the story softly, With earnest tones, and grave; Remember am the sinner Whom Jesus came to save; Tell me the story always If you would really be, In any time of trouble, A comforter to me.
Yoruba Lyrics: So tan naa fun mi jeeje, Ni ohun otito, Ranti p'elese l'emi, Ti Jesu wa gbala, So fun mi nigbakugba, Bi iwo yoo ba se Olutunu mi n'igba Ojo ibi ba de.

English Title: TELL ME THE OLD, OLD STORY
English Lyrics: Tell me the same old story When you have cause to fear That this world's empty glory Is costing me too dear; Yes, and when the world's glory Is dawning on my soul, Tell me the old, old story: “Christ Jesus makes thee Whole.”
Yoruba Lyrics: So itan kan naa fun mi Nigba t'o ba ri i pe Ogo asan aye yii Fe gba mi ni okan, Gba t’ogo oke orun Ba si n farahan mi, So tan laelae naa fun mi, “Kristi mu o l'arada.”

English Lyrics: Years I spent in vanity and pride, Caring not my Lord was crucified, Knowing not it was for me He Died On Calvary
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo lo odun pupo n'nu ese, Laibikita fun Oluwa mi, Laimo pe 'tori mi l'O se ku Ni kalfari.

English Lyrics: Mercy there was great and grace was free, Pardon there was multiply to me; There my burden'd soul found liberty, At Calvary,
Yoruba Lyrics: Aanu at'oore-ofe Re po, O dariji mi l'ofe nibe; Nibe l'eru okan mi fo lo, Ni Kalfari.

English Lyrics: By God's word at last my sin l’ learned, Then I trembled at the law I'd spurned, Till my guilty soul, imploring Turned To Calvary.
Yoruba Lyrics: Oro Re fi ese mi han mi, Mo wariri niwaju ofin, Titi okan ebi mi fi yi Si Kalfari.

English Lyrics: Now I've giving to Jesus everything, Now I gladly own Him as my King, Now my raptured soul can only sing Of Calvary
Yoruba Lyrics: Mo ti fi gbogbo re fun Jesu, Mo ti gba A l'Oluwa at'Oba, Okan mi n yo mo si n ko orin Ti Kalfari.

English Lyrics: Oh! the love that draws salvation's plan Oh! the grace that brought it down to man, Oh! the mighty gulf that God did span
Yoruba Lyrics: Aa! Ife iyanu t'o gba mi, Oor'ofe t'o wa mi l'awari, Ogiri ikele ni ti wo Ni Kalfari.

English Lyrics: Face to face with Christ, my Saviour, Face to face what will it be? When with rapture I behold Him, Jesus Christ who died for me!
Yoruba Lyrics: L'ojo kan n o ri Oluwa, A o padeloju-koju; Ngo maa wo ogo didan Re, Eni t' O ra mi pada.

English Lyrics: Face to face I shall behold Him, Far beyond the starry sky; Face to face, in all His glory, I shall see Him by and by!
Yoruba Lyrics: Ngo pade Re loju-koju, Ngo wo 'nu isinmi lo; Loju-koju n'nu ogo Re, L'emi yoo ri I nigboose.

English Lyrics: Only faintly now I see Him, With the darkling veil between; But a blessed day is coming, When His glory shall be seen.
Yoruba Lyrics: Nisinsinyi mo n w'oju Re Bii ninu awojiji, Sugbon ojo kan n bo wa, T’a o foju ri ogo Re

English Lyrics: What rejoicing in His presence, When are banished grief and pain, When the crooked ways are straightened And the dark things shall be plain.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ngo bu s'ayo n'iwaju Re Ekun 'rora yoo fo lo; Oru idanwo yoo koja, Ooro isegun yoo de.

English Lyrics: Face to face O blissful moment! Face to face to see and know; Face to face with my Redeemer, Jesus Christ who loves me so!
Yoruba Lyrics: Face to face O blissful moment! Face to face to see and know; Face to face with my Redeemer, Jesus Christ who loves me so!

English Lyrics: There's a land that is fairer than day, And by faith we can see it afar, For the Father waits over the way To prepare us a dwellingplace there.
Yoruba Lyrics: Ile kan n be t'o dara julo A le f'igbagbo ri i l'okere, Nibi ti Baba n duro de wa, Lati fun wa n'ibugbe nibe.

English Lyrics: In the sweet by and by We shall meet on the beautiful shore; In the sweet by and by, We shall meet on that beautiful shore.
Yoruba Lyrics: Pel'ayo, nigboose, L'a o pade l'ebute didannaa; Pel'ayo, nigboose, L'a o pade l'ebute didan naa.

English Lyrics:
We shall sing on that beautiful shore The melodious songs of the blest; And our spirit shall sorrow no More 
Not a sign for the blessing of 
Rest.
Yoruba Lyrics: A o ko 'rin l'ebute didan naa. Orin t'awon alabukunfun; Ko ni s'ibanuje fun wa mo, Kiki 'sinmi didun at' ayo.

English Lyrics: To our bountiful Father above We will offer our tribute of praise, For the glorious gift of His love And the blessing that hallow our days.
Yoruba Lyrics: A o ko'rin iyin si Baba wa, Fun oore-ofe Re l'ori wa, Fun ebun ofe ti Omo Re, At'ibukun t'a ko le ka tan.

English Lyrics: Lord, as of old at Pentecost Thou didst Thy pow'r display, With cleansing, purifying flame Descend on us today.
Yoruba Lyrics: B'I wo ti se ni Pentikosti, T'Iwo ran agbara, Agbara ti n so di mimo, Joo, ran An si wa l'onii…

English Lyrics: Lord, send the old time pow'r The Pentecostal pow'r! Thy floodgates of blessing on us throw open wide! Lord, send the old-time pow'r, the Pentecostal pow'r That sinners be converted And Thy name be glorified!
Yoruba Lyrics: Ran agbar'Emi Re, Ti ojo Pentikosti Si ferese orun, ro'jo ibukun Re! Ran agbar'Emi Re, Ti ojo Penticosti K'a le gb'elese la, Fun ogo oruko Re.

English Lyrics: For mighty works for Thee prepare And strengthen ev'ry heart; Come, take possession of Thine own, And never-more depart.
Yoruba Lyrics: Pese wa fun ise-yanu, Mu okan gbogbo le, Wa joba ninu okan wa, Ma fi wa sile mo.

English Lyrics: All self consumed, all sin destroyed! With earnest zeal endue Each waiting heart to work for Thee, O Lord, our faiths renew!
Yoruba Lyrics: Pa gbogbo ise ara run, Pa ese run n'nu wa, Fun wa ni igbina okan, Ti a o ma fi sin O.

English Lyrics: Speak, Lord! before Thy throne we wait, Thy promise we believe, And will not let Thee go until The blessing was received!
Yoruba Lyrics: Ba wa soro ki a to lo A ro mo leri Re, Awa ki yoo kuro nihin, Lair' ibukun Re gba!

English Title: LET JESUS COME INTO YOUR HEART
English Lyrics: If you are tired of the load of your sin, Let Jesus come into your heart; If you desire a new life to begin; Let Jesus come into your heart.
Yoruba Lyrics: B'eru ese re ba n wo o l'orun, Pe Jesu wo 'le okan re; Bi o ba n fe igbe aye titun, Pe Jesu wo le' okan re.

English Title: LET JESUS COME INTO YOUR HEART
English Lyrics: Just now, your doubtings give o'er; Just now, reject Him no more; Just now, throw open the door; Let Jesus come into your heart
Yoruba Lyrics: Le 'yemeji re sonu' Wa, b'Oluwa re la ja; Si okan re paya fun un; Pe Jesu wo 'le okan re

English Title: LET JESUS COME INTO YOUR HEART
English Lyrics: If 'tis for purity now that you sigh, Let Jesus come into your heart; Fountains for cleansing are flowing nearby, Let Jesus come into your heart.
Yoruba Lyrics: Bi o ba n wa iwenumo kiri, Pe Jesu wo le okan re; Omi wenumo ko jina si o, Pe Jesu wo le okan re.

English Title: LET JESUS COME INTO YOUR HEART
English Lyrics:
If there's a tempest your voice cannot still, Let Jesus come into your 
heart;
If there is a void this world 
never can fill,
Let Jesus come into your heart.
Yoruba Lyrics:
B'igbi wahala ba n gba o kiri, Pe Jesu wo 'le okan re; B'alafo ba wa t'aye ko le di,
Pe Jesu wo 'le Okan re.

English Title: LET JESUS COME INTO YOUR HEART
English Lyrics: If you would join the glad songs of the blest, Let Jesus come into your heart; If you would enter the mansions of rest, Let Jesus come into your heart
